# Routing and i18n Rules

- Follow the existing React Router v7 pattern in this project.
- Do not introduce loader/action/data-router patterns unless the project already uses them.
- Keep route-level logic near existing route files.
- Store shareable UI state in URL search params when appropriate.
- Keep temporary UI state local to components.
- Do not duplicate route-related fetching in multiple places.
- Do not hardcode user-facing text when nearby code uses i18next.
- Use existing `react-i18next` patterns.
- Keep translation keys consistent with existing naming.
- Use `Intl.DateTimeFormat` and `Intl.NumberFormat` for user-facing dates and numbers when relevant.
